    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted this package based on satisfactory quantitative validation results (E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs) and adequate achievement of 12 of 13 credibility factors. One factor (Test conditions) was below required level due to single-condition testing; this gap was accepted given the standardized nature of ASTM F1717. One factor (Relevance of the validation activities to the COU) was not assessed in this cycle, as the team considered formal COU relevance mapping to be beyond the scope of the current submission. The overall credibility was judged sufficient for the Medium assurance level at modelRiskLevel 3, with the understanding that the not-assessed factor represents a deferred activity.",
